Imposter syndrome is the belief that one’s success, achievements or situation are not deserved. This belief is accompanied by feelings of inadequacy, unworthiness or fraudulence

Successful people are often challenged with imposter syndrome and it can affect the quality of their work or negatively affect their viewpoint. This video will explain more about imposter syndrome.
